s, looking at: migration and multiculturalism; the care of young children; and home-based childcare and transnational dynamics. The book is unusual in weaving together the topics of migration and childcare and in studying these issues together within a gendered citizenship framework. It also demonstrates the value of a multi-level conceptualisation of citizenship, stretching from the domestic sphere through the national and European levels to the global. The book is aimed at students of social policy, sociology, European studies, women's studies and politics and at researchers/scholars/policy analysts in the areas of citizenship, gender, welfare states and migration.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aCitizenshipxSex differenceszEurope, Western. 0aImmigrantsxServices forzEurope, Western. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Gender Studies.2bisacsh1 aAnttonen, Anneli, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aGerhard, Ute, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aHeinen, Jacqueline, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aJohansson, Stina, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aLeira, Arnlaug, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aSiim, Birte, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aTobio, Constanza, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aWilliams, Fiona, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 awithGavanas, Anna, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-1995z97831111962130 cprintz978186134693340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781847422378423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781847422378/original  a978-3-11-11